  "text": "We previously showed that heterozygous loss-of-function mutations in the human mineralocorticoid receptor cause adPHA1 [CITATION_1] . With the inclusion of the kindreds described here, 22 different disease-causing mutations in MR have been identified in 24 adPHA1 kindreds. It has been proposed that adPHA1 is genetically heterogeneous on the basis of the failure to identify disease-causing mutations in MR after sequencing of . Genotype-phenotype correlations in adPHA1. Clinical characterization of kindreds PHA15 and PHA16. Individuals who carry the Arg537X mutation (E) were compared with their unaffected relatives (Ⅺ) for clinical indices of aldosterone effect, including systolic BP (SBP; mmHg), diastolic BP (DBP; mmHg), serum Na (mEq/L), serum K (mEq/L), fractional excretion of sodium (FENa), and serum aldosterone (ng/dl). Individual data points are shown, and the means of the recordings for affected and unaffected individuals (ϮSEM) are indicated by F and f, respectively. There was no significant difference between affected and unaffected family members for any of these indices, except for serum aldosterone levels, for which the difference was highly significant (P Ͻ 0.001).",
